[b]Triangle Compression Scanner Pro[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Slides a fixed-size window of confirmed swings across the chart and fits two boundary lines — an upper line from the window's outer highs, a lower line from its outer lows — to find compressing triangles: symmetric, ascending, or descending. Every distinct, non-overlapping valid triangle found is scored 0-100 and tracked independently until a confirmed breakout resolves it.

[b]Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Structure — boundary slopes match a valid triangle shape (symmetric/ascending/descending)
[*]Compression — real narrowing ratio end-to-start, monotonic through the midpoint
[*]Touch quality — how many of the window's highs/lows actually respect their boundary, not just the two defining points
[*]Line quality — for symmetric triangles, boundary slopes within a sane magnitude ratio of each other
[*]Duration — the window spans a meaningful number of bars, not a degenerate cluster
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Sliding-window search across the depth range, not a fixed point count
[*]Tracks multiple simultaneously valid, non-overlapping triangles at once
[*]Live breakout tracking — either boundary breaking resolves the pattern, with a directional alert
[*]Score-breakdown debug table for threshold tuning
[*]Dashboard with status, active pattern count, best score, type and window size
[/list]

